'''Muhammad Bayu Pangisthu''' (born 24 February 1996) is an [[Indonesia]]n badminton player.<ref name="PBSI - Bayu Pangisthu Biografi">{{cite web|url=http://www.badmintonindonesia.org/app/profile/aktif.aspx?id=000006926|title=Bayu Pangisthu Biografi|publisher=[[Badminton Association of Indonesia]]|accessdate=26 April 2014|language=Indonesian}}</ref> He is from [[PB Djarum|PB. Djarum]], a badminton club in [[Kudus, Kudus|Kudus]], [[Central Java]] and has been with the club since 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pbdjarum.org/profil/pemain/m/5ffb224d82a2513255/muhammad-bayu-pangisthu|title=Profile: Muhammad Bayu Pangisthu|publisher=[[PB Djarum]]|accessdate=15 July 2017|language=Indonesian}}</ref>

== Career ==
In 2012 he participated at the Indonesia Open Grand Prix Gold. In 2013 he participated at the Vietnam Open and at the Indonesia Open Grand Prix Gold; in 2014 at the World junior championships. In 2013 he was a finalist at the Maldives International.

